				<h2>Begin.fm</h2>
				<h3><a href="http://www.beginfm.co/" target="_blank">Launch the site</a></h3>
				<p>
					My journey with this project start early January of 2016. I was really inspired by a few great podcast stations that I listen to almost every week. For example <a href="https://spec.fm/podcasts/design-details" target="_blank">Design Details</a>, <a href="https://spec.fm/podcasts/does-not-compute" target="_blank">Does Not Compute</a>, and <a href="http://fourhourworkweek.com/podcast/" target="_blank">The Tim Ferris Show</a>, just to name a few. I know I couldn't compete with these amazing shows. The only way I could make this work is if I had a story to tell unique to my perspective. But, I had no clue as to what that would be. What I did know was who I wanted to have on the show. I wanted to have other creatives to share their stories and resources. Now, here's the problem...I had nothing in return for these folks. No audience, no money, nothing. I of course thought to my self, who on the hell would want to come and do a podcast with a random dude that has nothing to offer in return? Not to mention, what equipment would I use? How was I going to records? and plenty of other questions. 
					<br>
					This idea simmered in my head for a few months until one day I pretty much said, fuck it! And reached out to a rad developer and asked him if he wanted to record a show for my pretend podcast. I held my breath waiting for a hard no...But, to my surprise. He said yes. Holly cow, this is about to happen. I grabbed my headphones sent him a <a href="https://www.uberconference.com/" target="_blank">UberConference</a> link and started to record our conversation. And from there, <a href="http://www.beginfm.co/" target="_blank">Begin.fm</a> was born... 
				<p>
